obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line 2
  line `THE AFRICAN DEVELOPMENT BANK ACT, 1983`
  line `A CT N O.13 OF 1983`
  line `[26 th May, 1983. ]`
  line `An Act to implement the international agreement for the establishment and operation of the`
  line `African Development Bank and for matters concerned therewith.`
  line `B E it enacted by Parliament in the Thirty - fourth Year of the Republic of India as follows: —`
  line `1. Short title, extent and commencement. — ( 1 ) This Act may be called the African Development`
  line `Bank Act, 1983.`
  line `( 2 ) It extends to the whole of India.`
  line `( 3 ) It shall come into force on such date 1 as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
  line `2. Definitions. — In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires, —`
  line `( a ) “ Agreement ” means the agreement for the establishment of the African Developm ent Bank;`
  line `( b ) “ Bank ” means the African Development Bank established under the Agreement.`
  line `3. Payments to Bank. — ( 1 ) There shall be paid out of the Consolidated Fund of India, after due`
  line `appropriation made by Parliament by law in this behalf, all such sums as may, from time to time, be`
  line `required for the purpose of paying, —`
  line `( a ) the subscriptions payable by the Central Government to the Bank under Articles 6, 7, 10 and`
  line `21 of the Agreement;`
  line `( b ) any sums payable by the Central Government to the Bank under Article 28 of the Agreement;`
  line `( 2 ) The Central Government may, if it thinks fit so to do, create and issue to the Bank, in such form as`
  line `it thinks fit, any non - interest bearing and non - negotiable notes or other obligations.`
  line `4. Reserve Bank to be depository for Bank. — The Reserve Bank of India shall be the depository of`
  line `the Indian currency holdings of the Bank.`
  line `5. Conferment of status and certain immunities, exemptions and privileges on Bank and`
  line `conferment of certain immunities, exemptions and privileges on its officers and`
  line `employees. — ( 1 ) Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in any o ther law, the provisions of`
  line `the Agreement set out in the Schedule shall have the force of law in India;`
  line `Provided that nothing in Article 57 of the Agreement shall be construed as —`
  line `( a ) entitling the Bank to import into India goods free of any duty of customs without any`
  line `restriction on their subsequent sale therein; or`
  line `( b ) conferring on the Bank any exemption from duties or taxes which form part of the price of`
  line `goods sold; or`
  line `( c ) conferring on the Bank any exemption from duties or taxes which are in fact no more than`
  line `charges for services rendered.`
  line `( 2 ) The Central Government may, by notification in the O fficial Gazette, amend the Schedule in`
  line `conformity with any amendments, duly made and adopt ed, of the provisions of the Agreement set out`
  line therein.
  line `6. Power to make rules. — The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules for carrying out the purposes of this Act.`
  line `7. Notifications issued under section 5 and rules made under section 6 to be laid before`
  line `Parliament. — Every notification issued under sub - section ( 2 ) of section 5 and every rule made under`
  line `section 6 shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is issued or made, before each of the House of`
  line `Parliament, while i t is in session, for a total period of thirty days which m ay be comprised in one session`
  line `1. 15th December, 1983, vid e notification No. G.S.R. 889(E), dated 14th December, 1983, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary,`
  line `Part II, sec. 3( i ).`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
