obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line 3
  line `or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the`
  line `session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both House s agr ee in making any modification in the`
  line `notification or, as the case may be, in the rule or both Houses agree that the notification or rule should not`
  line `be issued or made, the notification or rule shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of`
  line `no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without`
  line `prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that notification or rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-4
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Page 4`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  sourcePage 4
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line 4
  line `THE SCHEDULE`
  line `( See section 5)`
  line `PROVISIONS OF THE AGREEMENT WHICH SHALL HAVE FORCE OF LAW`
  line `AGREEMENT ESTABLISHING THE AFRICAN DEVELOPMENT BANK`
  line `CHAPTER VII`
  line `S TATUS I MMUNITIES, E XEMPTIONS AND P RIVILEGES`
  line `ARTICLE 50`
  line `S TATUS`
  line `To enable it to fulfil its purpose and the functions with which it is entrusted, the Bank shall possess`
  line `full international personality. To those ends, it may enter into agreements with members, non - member`
  line `States and other international organi s ations. To the same ends, the statu s, immunities, exemptions and`
  line `privileges set forth in this Chapter shall be accorded to the Bank in the territory of each member.`
  line `ARTICLE 51`
  line `S TATUS IN M EMBER C OUNTRIES`
  line `In the territory of each member the Bank shall possess full judicial personality and, in particular, full`
  line `capacity:`
  line `( a ) to cont r act`
  line `( b ) to acquire and dispose of immovable and movable property; and`
  line `( c ) to institute legal proceedings.`
  line `ARTICLE 52`
  line `J UDICIAL P ROCEEDINGS`
  line `1. The Bank shall enjoy immunity from every form of legal process except in cases arising out of the`
  line `exercise of its borrowing powers when it may be sued only in a court of competent jurisdiction in the`
  line `territory of a member in which the Bank has its principa l office, or in the territory of a member or`
  line `non - member State where it has appointed an agent for the purpose of accepting service or notice of`
  line `process or has issued or guaranteed securities. No actions shall, however, be brought by members or`
  line `persons acting for or deriving claims from members.`
  line `2. The property and assets of the Bank shall, wherever located and by whomsoever held, be immune`
  line `from all forms of seizure, attachment or execution before the delivery of final judgment against the Bank.`
  line `ARTICLE 53`
  line `I MMUNITY OF A SSETS AND A RCHIVES`
  line `1. Property and assets of the Bank, wherever located and by whomsoever held, shall be immune from`
  line `search, requisition, confiscation, expropriation or any other form of taking or foreclosure by executive or`
  line `legislative action.`
  line `2. The archives of the Bank and, in general, all documents belonging to it, or held by it, shall be`
  line `inviolable, wherever located.`
  line `ARTICLE 54`
  line `F REED OM OF A SSETS FRO M R ESTRICTION`
  line `To the extent necessary to carry out the purpose and functions of the Bank and subject to the`
  line `provisions of this Agreement, all property and other assets of the Bank shall be exempt from restrictions,`
  line `regulations, controls and moratoria of any nature.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-5
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Page 5`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  sourcePage 5
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line 5
  line `A RTICLE 55`
  line `P RIVILEGE FOR C OMMUNICATIONS`
  line `Official communications of the Bank shall be accorded by each member the same treatment that it`
  line `accords to the official communications of other members.`
  line `ARTICLE 56`
  line `P ERS ONAL I MMUNITIES AND P RIVILEGES`
  line `1. All governors, directors, alternates, officers and employees of the Bank and experts and consultants`
  line `performing missions for the Bank;`
  line `( i ) shall be immune from legal process with respect to acts performed by them in their official`
  line capacity;
  line `( ii ) where they are not local nationals, shall be accorded the same immunities from immigration`
  line `restrictions, alien registration requirements and national service obligations, and the same facilities as`
  line `regards exchange regulations as are accorded by members to the representatives, officials and`
  line `employees of comparable rank of other members; and`
  line `( iii ) shall be granted the same treatment in respect of travelling facilities as is accorded by`
  line `members to representatives, officials and employees of comparable rank of other members.`
  line `2. Experts and consultants performing missions for the Ba nk shall be accorded such immunities and`
  line `privileges as are, in the opinion of the Bank, necessary for the independent exercise of their functions`
  line `during the period of their mission, including the time spent on journeys in connection therewith.`
  line `ARTICLE 57`
  line `E XEMPTION FROM T AXATION`
  line `1. The Bank, its property, other assets, income and its operations and transactions shall be exempt`
  line `from all taxation and from all customs duties. The Bank shall also be exempt from any obligation relating`
  line `to the payment, withholding or collection of any tax or duty.`
  line `2. No tax shall be levied on or in respect of salaries and emoluments paid by the Bank, to directors,`
  line `alternates, officers and other professional staff of the Bank.`
  line `3. No tax of any kind shall be levied on any obligation or security issued by the Bank, including any`
  line `dividend or interest thereon, by whomsoever held:`
  line `( i ) which discriminates against such obligation or security solely because it is issued by the Bank;`
  line or
  line `( ii ) if the sole jurisdictional basis for such taxation is the place or currency in which it is issued,`
  line `made payable or paid, or the location of any office or place of business maintained by the Bank.`
  line `4. No tax of any kind shall be levied on any obligation or security guaranteed by the Bank, including`
  line `any divid end or interest thereon, by whomsoever held:`
  line `( i ) which discriminates against such obligation or security solely because it is guaranteed by the`
  line `Bank; or`
  line `( ii ) if the sole jurisdictional basis for such taxation is the location of any office or place of`
  line `busin ess maintained by the Bank.`
  line `ARTICLE 58`
  line `N OTIFICATION OF I MPLEMENTATION`
  line `Each member shall promptly inform the Bank of the specific action which it has taken to make`
  line `effective in its territory the provisions of this Chapter.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-6
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Page 6`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  sourcePage 6
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line 6
  line `ARTICLE 59`
  line `A PPLICATION OF I MMUNIT IES, E XEMPTIONS AND P RIVILEGES`
  line `The immunities, exemptions and privileges provided in this Chapter are granted in the interests of the`
  line `Bank. The Board of Directors may waive, to such extent and upon such conditions as it may determine,`
  line `the immunities and exemptions provided in Articles 52, 54, 56 and 57 of this Agreement in cases where`
  line `its action would in its opinion further the interests of the Bank. The President shall have the right and the`
  line `duty to waive the immunity of any official in cases where, in h is opinion, the immunity would impede the`
  line `course of justice and can be waived without prejudice to the interests of the Bank.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
